data: {"model":"brave-pro","system_fingerprint":"","choices":[{"delta":{"role":"assistant","content":"<answer>{\"answer\": \"As of May 4, 2026, the temporary ceasefire between the United States and Iran, which began on April 8, 2026, is on the brink of collapse amid renewed military actions and escalating rhetoric. Despite President Donald Trump declaring on May 1 that \\\"hostilities\\\" with Iran had \\\"terminated\\\" to meet the War Powers Act deadline, both sides have engaged in hostile acts in the past 24 hours, testing the fragile truce.\\n\\nOn May 4, the US Navy destroyed six Iranian military speedboats in the Strait of Hormuz that were allegedly threatening commercial vessels, with US Central Command confirming the operation. In response, Iranian state media claimed that a US warship near Jask was hit by two missiles, a claim the Pentagon denied, stating no US vessel was struck. Additionally, a South Korean-operated vessel suffered a fire and explosion in the strait, though the cause remains unclear.\\n\\nIran has intensified pressure by launching missiles and drones toward UAE infrastructure, with the UAE reporting it engaged 19 Iranian missiles and drones; an oil facility fire was attributed to an Iranian drone attack. Iran\\u2019s actions follow its submission of a 14-point peace plan, delivered via Pakistani intermediaries, calling for a complete end to the war within 30 days, withdrawal of US forces from Iran\\u2019s periphery, lifting of sanctions and the naval blockade, release of frozen assets, and a new governance mechanism for the Strait of Hormuz.\\n\\nPresident Trump has rejected the proposal, calling it \\u201cnot acceptable,\\u201d and reiterated threats that Iranian forces would be \\u201cblown off the face of the Earth\\u201d if they target US ships. He also launched \\u201cProject Freedom\\u201d to escort ships through the Strait, which Iran condemns as a ceasefire violation, asserting that the strait is under its sovereign control.\\n\\nThe Strait of Hormuz remains effectively closed, with traffic reduced to fewer than 10 daily transits\\u2014down from over 100 pre-war\\u2014with Iran selectively allowing only navy or approved diplomatic vessels. The US maintains a naval blockade of Iranian ports since April 13, 2026, costing Iran nearly $5 billion, while Iran blocks commercial access to the strait.\\n\\nThe humanitarian toll is severe: over 3.2 million Iranians have been displaced, more than 2,300 civilians killed, and 32,300 injured as of early April, with 481 schools damaged and widespread destruction of civilian infrastructure. The conflict has also expanded into Lebanon, where fighting between Hezbollah and Israel has killed over 2,000 people.\\n\\nDespite diplomatic efforts, including Pakistan-mediated talks, Iran has refused to engage, accusing the US of ceasefire violations. The war, which began on February 28, 2026, after a US-Israeli strike killed Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei, remains in a dangerous stalemate with no resolution in sight.\"}</answer>"},"finish_reason":null}],"created":1777974994,"id":"4a2ad252-e647-4000-93a3-29bc2245e96f","object":"chat.completion.chunk","usage":null}

